  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2075",
  "title": "Add numeric facet to searchParameters",
  "body": "Hi there, \r\n\r\nEach of my search results has a publish date. I want to ensure that nothing with a publish date in the future shows in my results. Is there currently a way to do this using the searchParameters? Here is my current setup:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst searchParametersVideo = {\r\n  facetFilters: [[\"modelName:video\"], [\"locale:\" + getAlgoliaLocale(locale)], [\"publishDate:\"+'<='+moment().format()]],\r\n  hitsPerPage: 3\r\n};\r\n\r\nreturn (\r\n  <InstantSearch\r\n    appId={config.search.appId}\r\n    apiKey={config.search.apiKey}\r\n    searchParameters={searchParametersVideo}\r\n    searchState={{query: this.props.searchState}}\r\n    indexName={config.search.index}>\r\n    <VirtualSearchBox/>\r\n    <VideoResults />\r\n  </InstantSearch>\r\n)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs you can see, I have attempted to add a publishDate filter to my `facetFilters`, which does not seem to work. Does anyone know of the correct way to do this?\r\n\r\nThank you, \r\nJoshua",
